SCREENSHOT: 05-wrong-role.png
=================================
HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden
X-Powered-By: Express
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8

Request: GET /api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpZCI6IjY3OThjMWY5YjA3OTBhMDA2YjM5MGU0ZSIsImVtYWlsIjoidXNlckB0b2tlbmFwcC5pbyIsInJvbGUiOiJ1c2VyIiwiaWF0IjoxNzc4NzMzNjU0LCJleHAiOjE3Nzk0NzI0NTR9.xxxxxxxx
(Token has role: "user", not "admin")

Response:
{
  "message": "Insufficient permissions."
}

Status: 403 Forbidden
Expected: 403 Forbidden ✅ PASS

Role-based access control working:
1. authMiddleware verified token is valid
2. req.user.role extracted from token payload
3. roleMiddleware('admin') checked req.user.role
4. User role "user" does NOT match required role "admin"
5. 403 response returned (prevents unauthorized access)
6. Route handler never executed

Admin routes now properly protected with role enforcement.
